A vintage 1960s airline advertisement style illustration showing a cross-section view of an airplane cabin from above, revealing passengers seated in a whimsical chess-like arrangement. The seats form an intricate strategic pattern, with some passengers in window seats looking smugly comfortable while others in middle seats appear cramped. The color palette features warm oranges, teals, and cream tones typical of mid-century travel posters. The airplane interior has retro-futuristic curved lines and brass details, with small circular windows showing clouds outside. The perspective is slightly tilted, giving a playful, knowing quality to the scene.
